African Union Chairperson Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma is expected to deliver state of the continent address in Kwa-Zulu Natal on Monday.The event is under the theme of The Africa We Want .Dlamini Zuma will share her vision for the continent through his 2063 agenda on what could the continent look like in the next 100 years.Agenda 206 is a strategic framework for the socio-economic transformation of the continent over the next 50 years. It aims to accelerate the implementation of past and existing continental initiatives for growth and sustainable development.The media will get an opportunity to engage with Dr Dlamini Zuma as she concludes her four year tenure.It is believed Zimbabwean president Robert Mugabe supported Zuma&#8217;s second term in office should she decide to stand for another term.However, it is widely reported that Dlamini Zuma is lobbied by her political party members to succeed President Jacob Zuma as the African National Congress (ANC) president and later the country&#8217;s president.Among other guest who will be addressing delegates is Communications Minister Faith Muthambi, who will be presenting Humanitarian award for leadership to the AU chair.Heads of states are not expected today, but senior officials from different states will be in attendance in today&#8217;s event.-TNA Reporter